<br>
Saddam is just an unfortunate first victim of the modern political era.  He has made countless mistakes after mistakes based on how he expected America to react.  His gambles simply did not pay off or pan out as he intended.  <br>
<br>
It is premature to speculate but more than likely he wanted to become a stronger <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>looking</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> world power if people thought he had WMD.  Its all about appearances.  Paying a few thousand to actors here, running out a few annoying dissidents there, and you have a far cheaper political bargaining chip than dropping billions into an actual program.<br>
<br>
But like the Gulf War, America called his bluff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fireandfury.org" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.fireandfury.org/ermoksig1.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kurley>Kurley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1082<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=697.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Iraqi pre-war intelligence</span><hr size=1> If you buy into this, then there is a large metal, pyramid like structure nestled in the heart of Paris that I'd love to sell you for a great bargain.<br>
<br>
First - middle eastern dictators/leaders do not fall back upon &quot;paper tigers&quot; as their &quot;last line&quot; of defense or intimidation.  Middle eastern doctrine and politics eschews bullshit &quot;bluffs&quot;.<br>
<br>
Second - why would Saddam pretend to have WMD's when he could have quite easily purchased as many as his heart desired?<br>
<br>
Third - to assume that Saddam concluded that an allied power would never call his bluff is again inconsistent with middle eastern politics:  if you make a threat, you must be prepared to back it up.  Anything less is cowardice.<br>
<br>
Fourth - this: &quot;Then, because they believe it, they pass polygraph tests ... and the planted information becomes true to the West even if it was all made up to deceive us,&quot; the senior intelligence official said.&quot;<br>
<br>
Any basic intelligence asset (and most certainly an operative such as a &quot;double agent&quot; or &quot;false flag&quot;) is trained and conditioned to deal with polygraphs (i.e. have it indicate lies when the truth is being told and vice versa).  <br>
<br>
Fifth - this is simply the flavour of the month in terms of explaining why the principal reason for invading Iraq (i.e. WMD) has not, in fact, revealed any WMD.  <br>
<br>
US intelligence is the most sophisticated intelligence engine in the world - the budget of the NSA alone, dwarfs that of many countries.  Christ, even in the World War 2 era, US and British intelligence had many techniques for uncovering &quot;double agents&quot;, false defectors, and corroborating the intelligence provided by them to separate the &quot;thorns&quot; and the &quot;lead&quot; from the &quot;roses&quot; and the &quot;gold&quot;.  <br>
<br>
To assume that US intelligence hasn't grown and improved geometrically since the 1940's, and that the entire military and intelligence community was duped by a few of Saddam's agents, with bogus paperwork is naivety in the extreme.<br>
<br>
However, just like pin the tail on the donkey, the kids keep stabbing the tail into something until it sticks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syllestraefv>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3582<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 12:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=697.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Iraqi pre-war intelligence</span><hr size=1> ?<br>
